projects within the consumer sector it invests in suppliers of consumer goods and retail businesses and in leisure it focuses on travel gaming and entertainment industries including pubs clubs restaurants and other leisure venues within healthcare segment the firm prefers to invest in the areas of healthcare services medical technologies pharmaceutical services healthcare technology and software in industrial sector it seeks to invest in industrial and manufacturing of automotives specialized engineering or distribution chemicals electrical and electronics mechanical engineering industries specialist consumer product design and manufacture the services sector focuses on outsourcing professional services facilities management staffing social care services and logistics businesses the tmt team primarily invests in the technology and media sectors and selectively in niches of the telecoms sector within software electronics and semiconductor markets the investment focus is on productbased companies with high intellectual property content within the media sector the investment focus is on bb publishing and other high intellectual property companies including those driven by the internet the firm also invests in vertical market application software and outsourcing for industry verticals such as telecommunications financial services and healthcare it considers investments in tmt companies with enterprise value between £ million  million and £ million  million and buyouts in services and industrials sectors with enterprise value between £ million  million and £ million  million it seeks to make investments in the companies based in western and northern europe with a focus on united kingdom nordic region denmark finland iceland norway sweden germany france italy ireland portugal spain and the belgium luxembourg and netherlands region it typically invests between £ million  million and £ million  million in companies which have enterprise values between £ million  million and £ million  million aiming to contribute around £ million  million of equity per transaction the firm seeks to invest in form of equity it can consider majority or minority stakes in its portfolio companies it seeks to sit on the board of its portfolio companies the firm was previously known as mercury private equity hgcapital was founded in  and is based in london united kingdom with additional offices in munich germany frankfurt germany and amsterdam netherlands detailed description  more london riversidelondon  se apunited kingdomfounded in  phone     fax     wwwhgcapitalnet key executives for hgcapital mr nicholas james humphries chief executive officer senior partner and head of tmt age  mr craig donaldson founding partner mr martin block partner and head of munich office and industrials team mr stephen bough partner head of the finance fund administration and legal  compliance and it functions mr steven batchelor partner associate director and head of client services compensation as of fiscal year  hgcapital key developments visma seeks acquisitions jun   visma as gives investors ongoing exposure to a leading provider of mission critical accounting resource planning and payroll software to small and mediumsized enterprises as well as the public sector in the nordic region hgcapital will continue to support the business going forward in order to grow revenues both organically and through acquisitions visma is one of the leading saas providers to smbs and the public sector in europe with the potential to accelerate this growth both through organic investment and further bolton acquisitions esendex mulls acquisitions jun   esendex limited is seeking acquisitions hgcapital has announced an investment in esendex geoff love chief executive officer of esendex said with hgcapital’s backing for further acquisitions as well as continuing strong organic growth we look forward to helping even more businesses transform their communications with their customers and staff” b